en sind. Der Band untersucht verschiedene dialogische Strategien des Lachens und Schweigens von höfischem Roman und Heldenepik bis zu Mären und Reiseberichten.  aThis volume presents contributions about laughter and silence as special forms of communication in medieval and early modern literature. Laughter and silence question what has been said or confirm it, frame or reflect it. This volume examines various dialogic strategies of laughter and silence, covering court romances and heroic epics as well as medieval short stories and travelogues.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aHöfische Kultur. 4aHöfische Literatur. 4aKommunikation, literarische. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMittelalter/Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aCommunication, Literary.  aCourt Culture.  aCourt Literature.  aEarly Modern Age.  aLiterary Studies.  aMiddle Ages/Literature.1 aBußmann, Astrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoxon, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichaelis, Beatrice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReichlin, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRöcke, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRöcke, Werner, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchnyder, Mireille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVelten, Hans Rudolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVelten, Hans Rudolf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:d